</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1162,1295,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,184,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-24@6.[205,1383,181,1823]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–25. Bebelis spp. 16–20) B. nearnsi sp. nov., holotype male: 16) Dorsal habitus; 17) Ventral habitus; 18) Lateral habitus; 19) Head, frontal view; 20) Lower eye lobe, lateral view. 21–23) B. pseudolignosa Breuning, 1942, female from Argentina (Salta, Rosario de Lerma): 21) Lower eye lobe, lateral view; 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Lateral habitus. 24) B. pseudolignosa, holotype, by Jesus Santiago Moure. 25) Dorcasta prolongata Fisher, 1947 (= B. lignea (Bates, 1866)), holotype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886408/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Figs 21–24</figureCitation>
), but differs as follows: distance between upper eye lobes about as wide as one upper lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1066,1152,1159,1186]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,184,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-24@6.[205,1383,181,1823]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–25. Bebelis spp. 16–20) B. nearnsi sp. nov., holotype male: 16) Dorsal habitus; 17) Ventral habitus; 18) Lateral habitus; 19) Head, frontal view; 20) Lower eye lobe, lateral view. 21–23) B. pseudolignosa Breuning, 1942, female from Argentina (Salta, Rosario de Lerma): 21) Lower eye lobe, lateral view; 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Lateral habitus. 24) B. pseudolignosa, holotype, by Jesus Santiago Moure. 25) Dorcasta prolongata Fisher, 1947 (= B. lignea (Bates, 1866)), holotype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886408/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); lower eye lobes longer than genae (
<figureCitation box="[288,373,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,184,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-24@6.[205,1383,181,1823]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–25. Bebelis spp. 16–20) B. nearnsi sp. nov., holotype male: 16) Dorsal habitus; 17) Ventral habitus; 18) Lateral habitus; 19) Head, frontal view; 20) Lower eye lobe, lateral view. 21–23) B. pseudolignosa Breuning, 1942, female from Argentina (Salta, Rosario de Lerma): 21) Lower eye lobe, lateral view; 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Lateral habitus. 24) B. pseudolignosa, holotype, by Jesus Santiago Moure. 25) Dorcasta prolongata Fisher, 1947 (= B. lignea (Bates, 1866)), holotype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886408/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
); central area of the elytra mostly with sparse brownish pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[1151,1235,1195,1222]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,184,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-24@6.[205,1383,181,1823]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–25. Bebelis spp. 16–20) B. nearnsi sp. nov., holotype male: 16) Dorsal habitus; 17) Ventral habitus; 18) Lateral habitus; 19) Head, frontal view; 20) Lower eye lobe, lateral view. 21–23) B. pseudolignosa Breuning, 1942, female from Argentina (Salta, Rosario de Lerma): 21) Lower eye lobe, lateral view; 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Lateral habitus. 24) B. pseudolignosa, holotype, by Jesus Santiago Moure. 25) Dorcasta prolongata Fisher, 1947 (= B. lignea (Bates, 1866)), holotype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886408/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); and elytral apex strongly obliquely truncate (
<figureCitation box="[466,549,1231,1258]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,184,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-24@6.[205,1383,181,1823]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–25. Bebelis spp. 16–20) B. nearnsi sp. nov., holotype male: 16) Dorsal habitus; 17) Ventral habitus; 18) Lateral habitus; 19) Head, frontal view; 20) Lower eye lobe, lateral view. 21–23) B. pseudolignosa Breuning, 1942, female from Argentina (Salta, Rosario de Lerma): 21) Lower eye lobe, lateral view; 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Lateral habitus. 24) B. pseudolignosa, holotype, by Jesus Santiago Moure. 25) Dorcasta prolongata Fisher, 1947 (= B. lignea (Bates, 1866)), holotype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886408/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1942" box="[598,791,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudolignosa">
<emphasis box="[598,791,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">B. pseudolignosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the distance between upper eye lobes is wider than width of one upper lobe (
<figureCitation box="[361,444,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,184,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-24@6.[205,1383,181,1823]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–25. Bebelis spp. 16–20) B. nearnsi sp. nov., holotype male: 16) Dorsal habitus; 17) Ventral habitus; 18) Lateral habitus; 19) Head, frontal view; 20) Lower eye lobe, lateral view. 21–23) B. pseudolignosa Breuning, 1942, female from Argentina (Salta, Rosario de Lerma): 21) Lower eye lobe, lateral view; 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Lateral habitus. 24) B. pseudolignosa, holotype, by Jesus Santiago Moure. 25) Dorcasta prolongata Fisher, 1947 (= B. lignea (Bates, 1866)), holotype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886408/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
), lower eye lobes are slightly shorter than genae (
<figureCitation box="[994,1075,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,184,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-24@6.[205,1383,181,1823]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–25. Bebelis spp. 16–20) B. nearnsi sp. nov., holotype male: 16) Dorsal habitus; 17) Ventral habitus; 18) Lateral habitus; 19) Head, frontal view; 20) Lower eye lobe, lateral view. 21–23) B. pseudolignosa Breuning, 1942, female from Argentina (Salta, Rosario de Lerma): 21) Lower eye lobe, lateral view; 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Lateral habitus. 24) B. pseudolignosa, holotype, by Jesus Santiago Moure. 25) Dorcasta prolongata Fisher, 1947 (= B. lignea (Bates, 1866)), holotype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886408/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) (according to Breuning (1942), they are slightly longer than genae, but, apparently, he measured using the frontal area of the genae, and not the true length), central area of the elytra mostly with yellowish-brown pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[1062,1193,1339,1365]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,184,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-24@6.[205,1383,181,1823]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–25. Bebelis spp. 16–20) B. nearnsi sp. nov., holotype male: 16) Dorsal habitus; 17) Ventral habitus; 18) Lateral habitus; 19) Head, frontal view; 20) Lower eye lobe, lateral view. 21–23) B. pseudolignosa Breuning, 1942, female from Argentina (Salta, Rosario de Lerma): 21) Lower eye lobe, lateral view; 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Lateral habitus. 24) B. pseudolignosa, holotype, by Jesus Santiago Moure. 25) Dorcasta prolongata Fisher, 1947 (= B. lignea (Bates, 1866)), holotype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886408/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Figs 22, 24</figureCitation>
), and the elytral apex is not strongly obliquely truncate, and is somewhat emarginate (
<figureCitation box="[863,946,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,184,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-24@6.[205,1383,181,1823]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–25. Bebelis spp. 16–20) B. nearnsi sp. nov., holotype male: 16) Dorsal habitus; 17) Ventral habitus; 18) Lateral habitus; 19) Head, frontal view; 20) Lower eye lobe, lateral view. 21–23) B. pseudolignosa Breuning, 1942, female from Argentina (Salta, Rosario de Lerma): 21) Lower eye lobe, lateral view; 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Lateral habitus. 24) B. pseudolignosa, holotype, by Jesus Santiago Moure. 25) Dorcasta prolongata Fisher, 1947 (= B. lignea (Bates, 1866)), holotype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886408/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2022" box="[965,1138,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nearnsi">
<emphasis box="[965,1138,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Bebelis nearnsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bates, 1866)" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lignea">
<emphasis box="[1336,1436,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">B. lignea</emphasis>
(Bates, 1866)
</taxonomicName>
by the body stouter, different elytral pubescent pattern, and elytral apex less projected (
<figureCitation box="[1280,1363,1411,1438]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,184,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-24@6.[205,1383,181,1823]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–25. Bebelis spp. 16–20) B. nearnsi sp. nov., holotype male: 16) Dorsal habitus; 17) Ventral habitus; 18) Lateral habitus; 19) Head, frontal view; 20) Lower eye lobe, lateral view. 21–23) B. pseudolignosa Breuning, 1942, female from Argentina (Salta, Rosario de Lerma): 21) Lower eye lobe, lateral view; 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Lateral habitus. 24) B. pseudolignosa, holotype, by Jesus Santiago Moure. 25) Dorcasta prolongata Fisher, 1947 (= B. lignea (Bates, 1866)), holotype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886408/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lignea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">B. lignea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the body is slender, the elytral pubescence has a different pattern, and the elytral apex is strongly projected (
<figureCitation box="[160,244,1482,1509]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,184,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-24@6.[205,1383,181,1823]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–25. Bebelis spp. 16–20) B. nearnsi sp. nov., holotype male: 16) Dorsal habitus; 17) Ventral habitus; 18) Lateral habitus; 19) Head, frontal view; 20) Lower eye lobe, lateral view. 21–23) B. pseudolignosa Breuning, 1942, female from Argentina (Salta, Rosario de Lerma): 21) Lower eye lobe, lateral view; 22) Dorsal habitus; 23) Lateral habitus. 24) B. pseudolignosa, holotype, by Jesus Santiago Moure. 25) Dorcasta prolongata Fisher, 1947 (= B. lignea (Bates, 1866)), holotype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886408/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
